This paper discusses conversational agents and their application in automated customer support, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The comparison of different models and their performance evaluation involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG), making cs.LG another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of simple information retrieval techniques, which falls under the category of computational complexity (CC), making cs.CC a possible sub-category as well.
